The weekly Federal Executive Council meeting has reportedly failed to hold on Wednesday at the Presidential Villa, Abuja.
The council, which comprises, Vice-President, Yemi Osinbajo, ministers and some top presidential aides is headed by President Muhammadu Buhari.
Reports say the meeting was not slated on the President’s schedule for the week.
ALSO SEE: Nigeria’s economy remains in crisis zone as oil production drops
More so, Buhari was absent at the last week’s meeting, fueling speculations that his health had deteriorated.
But the Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, dispelled the speculation, saying the President was hale and hearty.
Members meet weekly inside the Council Chambers of the Presidential Villa.

			
